&lt;Paperboard Industries Corp> said itagreed to sell 93 mln dlrs of convertible notes, with half tobe purchased by brokers Wood Gundy Inc and McLeod Young WeirLtd and the other half by controlling shareholder KinburnIndustrial Corp.    The notes will be convertible into six mln common shares at15.50 dlrs a share by September 30. Paperboard now has6,057,495 shares outstanding. Proceeds will be used partly tofinance the previously announced acquisition of Belkin Inc.Purchase of notes will be conditional on Paperboard acquiring98.2 pct of Belkin's shares from Balaclava Enterprises Ltd. Reuter&#3;